{
  "texts": [
    "Kernel methodsIn Gaussian processes (GPs), specifying a covariance (kernel) k determines a prior over functions and thereby encodes the inductive bias of the model.",
    "The predictive behavior of a GP depends critically on this choice: different kernels express different notions of similarity (e.g.",
    "smoothness, invariance, compositional structure) and thus suit different input types (e.g.",
    "strings, graphs, molecules).",
    "Kernel methods specify a positive-definite kernel k(x, x ′) that represents an inner product in a (possibly infinite-dimensional) feature space H, i.e."
  ]
}